16 In SZFNX v Minister for Immigration and Citizenship [2007] FCA 1980 , Besanko J considered fraud by an agent in the context of a Tribunal hearing. In that case, the appellant's signature had been falsely placed on the document and part of the appellant's statement had been made up. Justice Besanko said at [37] that those facts may go some way towards establishing fraud but that it is still necessary for the appellant to show that the fraud has affected the process described by the Migration Act 1958 (Cth). In this case, the matters raised by the appellant, namely:

• the fact that Mr Shi signed the form in the context of an authority to act;

• the fact that the appellant had not notified Mr Shi of his new address; and

• the fact that Mr Shi failed to tell the appellant about the Tribunal hearing;

do not constitute fraud on the Tribunal within the meaning of SZFDE and there is not sufficient evidence to support such a conclusion.
